name: Incoming traffic on interface $1
description: The number of octets in valid MAC frames received on this interface, including the MAC header and FCS.

name: Outgoing traffic on interface $1
description: The number of octets transmitted in MAC frames on this interface, including the MAC header and FCS.

name: Description of interface $1
description: A textual string containing information about the interface.  This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.

name: Operational status of interface $1
description: The current operational state of the interface.

name: Admin status of interface $1
description: The desired state of the interface.

name: Inbound errors on interface $1
description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.  For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

name: Outbound errors on interface $1
description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.

name: Number of network interfaces
description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

name: Device description
description: A textual description of the entity.  This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.

name: Device name
description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.  If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

name: Device location
description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').  If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

name: Device contact details
description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.  If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

name: Device uptime
description: The time since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

name: Description of storage $1
description: A description of the type and instance of the storage described by this entry.

name: Allocation units for storage $1
description: The size, in bytes, of the data objects allocated from this pool.  If this entry is monitoring sectors, blocks, buffers, or packets, for example, this number will commonly be greater than one.  Otherwise this number will typically be one.

name: Total disk space on $1 in units
description: The size of the storage represented by this entry, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits. This object is writable to allow remote configuration of the size of the storage area in those cases where such an operation makes sense and is possible on the underlying system. For example, the amount of main memory allocated to a buffer pool might be modified or the amount of disk space allocated to virtual memory might be modified.

name: Used disk space on $1 in units
description: The amount of the storage represented by this entry that is allocated, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits.

name: Total disk space on $1
description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get total disk space in bytes.

name: Used disk space on $1
description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get used disk space in bytes.

name: CPU $2 time
description: The time the CPU has spent running the kernel and its processes.

name: CPU $2 time
description: The time the CPU has spent running users' processes that are not niced.

name: Host name
description: System host name.

name: System information
description: The information as normally returned by 'uname -a'.

name: Number of logged in users
description: Number of users who are currently logged in.

name: Available memory
description: Available memory is defined as free+cached+buffers memory.

name: Network interface discovery
description: Discovery of network interfaces as defined in global regular expression "Network interfaces for discovery".

name: Values processed by Zabbix proxy per second
Network interface discovery
description: Discovery of network interfaces as defined in global regular expression "Network interfaces for discovery".

name: Discover VMware VMs
description: Discovery of guest virtual machines.

name: Ballooned memory
description: The amount of guest physical memory that is currently reclaimed through the balloon driver.

name: Compressed memory
description: The amount of memory currently in the compression cache for this VM.

name: Memory size
description: Total size of configured memory.

name: Swapped memory
description: The amount of guest physical memory swapped out to the VM's swap device by ESX.

name: Committed storage space
description: Total storage space, in bytes, committed to this virtual machine across all datastores.

name: Uncommitted storage space
description: Additional storage space, in bytes, potentially used by this virtual machine on all datastores.

name: Unshared storage space
description: Total storage space, in bytes, occupied by the virtual machine across all datastores, that is not shared with any other virtual machine.

name: CPU usage
description: Current upper-bound on CPU usage. The upper-bound is based on the host the virtual machine is current running on, as well as limits configured on the virtual machine itself or any parent resource pool. Valid while the virtual machine is running.

name: Number of virtual CPUs
description: Number of virtual CPUs assigned to the guest.

name: Power state
description: The current power state of the virtual machine.

name: Uptime
description: System uptime.

name: Discover VMware hypervisors
description: Discovery of hypervisors.

name: Bios UUID
description: The hardware BIOS identification.

name: CPU cores
description: Number of physical CPU cores on the host. Physical CPU cores are the processors contained by a CPU package.

name: CPU frequency
description: The speed of the CPU cores. This is an average value if there are multiple speeds. The product of CPU frequency and number of cores is approximately equal to the sum of the MHz for all the individual cores on the host.

name: CPU model
description: The CPU model.

name: CPU threads
description: Number of physical CPU threads on the host.

name: CPU usage
description: Aggregated CPU usage across all cores on the host in Hz. This is only available if the host is connected.

name: Full name
description: The complete product name, including the version information.

name: Model
description: The system model identification.

name: Overall status
description: The overall alarm status of the host: gray - unknown, ok, red - it has a problem, yellow - it might have a problem.

name: Total memory
description: The physical memory size.

name: Uptime
description: System uptime.

name: Used memory
description: Physical memory usage on the host.

name: Vendor
description: The hardware vendor identification.

name: Version
description: Dot-separated version string.

name: Number of guest VMs
description: Number of guest virtual machines.

name: Ballooned memory
description: The amount of guest physical memory that is currently reclaimed through the balloon driver. Sum of all guest VMs.

name: Hypervisor name
description: Hypervisor name of the guest VM.

name: Mounted filesystem discovery
description: Discovery of all guest file systems.

name: Guest memory usage
description: The amount of guest physical memory that is being used by the VM.

name: Host memory usage
description: The amount of host physical memory allocated to the VM, accounting for saving from memory sharing with other VMs.

name: Private memory
description: Amount of memory backed by host memory and not being shared.

name: Shared memory
description: The amount of guest physical memory shared through transparent page sharing.

name: Discover VMware clusters
description: Discovery of clusters

name: Cluster name
description: Cluster name of the guest VM.

name: Cluster name
description: Cluster name of the guest VM.

name: Disk device discovery
description: Discovery of all disk devices.

name: Network device discovery
description: Discovery of all network devices.

Average number of bytes written to {#DISKDESC}
Average read latency of the datastore $3
Average write latency of the datastore $3
Health state rollup
description: The host health state rollup sensor value: gray - unknown, ok, red - it has a problem, yellow - it might have a problem.
